rice Fisher\n| \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The House of Tomorrow (2017 film)|The House of Tomorrow]]''\n| Josephine Prendergast\n| Also executive producer\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[All I Wish]]''\n| Celia Berges\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Nostalgia (2018 film)|Nostalgia]]''\n| Helen Greer\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[The Tale]]''\n| Nettie\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[American Woman (2019 film)|American Woman]]''\n| Miss Dolly\n| \n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Lucy in the Sky]]''\n| Nana Holbrook\n| \n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Welcome to Pine Grove!]]''\n| Helen Wilson\n| ''Post-production''\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Pieces of a Woman]]''\n|\n| ''Filming''\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1958\n| ''[[Kraft Television Theatre]]''\n| Linda \n| Episode: \"Trick or Treat\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961 \n| ''[[Michael Shayne#Television|Michael Shayne]]''\n| Carol \n| Episode: \"Strike Out\"; credited as Ellen McRae<ref>\"Sports Celebrities Appear in Mystery\", Biddeford-Saco (Maine) Journal, March 4, 1961, p. 10.</ref> \n|-\n| 1961 \n| ''[[The Loretta Young Show]]''\n| Ann Walters\n| Episode: \"Woodlot\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961\n| ''[[Dr. Kildare (TV series)|Dr. Kildare]]''\n| Anne Garner \n| Episode: \"Second Chance\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961\n| ''[[Surfside 6]]''\n| Wandra Drake\n| Episode: \"Double Image\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961, 1963 \n| ''[[77 Sunset Strip]]''\n| Betty Benson (1961)<br>Sandra Keene (1963)\n| 2 episodes; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961\n| ''[[Cheyenne (1955 TV series)|Cheyenne]]''\n| Emmy Mae \n| Episode: \"Day's Pay\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1961\n| ''[[The Dick Powell Show]]''\n|Rose Maxon\n| Episode: \"Ricochet\"; credited as Ellen McRae\n|-\n| 1962,<br>1971\n| ''[[Gunsmoke]]''\n| Polly Mims (1962)<br>Amy Waters (1971)\n| 3 episodes; credited as Ellen McRae (1962), credited as Ellen Burstyn (1971)\n|-\n| 1962\n| ''[[Ben Casey]]''\n| Dr. Leslie Fraser (ep. 1)<br>Connie (ep. 2)\n| 2 e