ush with Fate]]''\n| Rika\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''{{sortname|The|Five People You Meet in Heaven}}''\n| Ruby\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''The Madam's Family: The Truth About the Canal Street Brothel''\n| Tommie\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''Our Fathers''\n| Mary Ryan\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Mrs. Harris]]''\n| Ex-lover No. 3 (Former Tarnower \"Steady\")\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The Book of Daniel (TV series)|The Book of Daniel]]''\n| Bishop Beatrice Congreve\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Oprah Winfrey Presents: Mitch Albom's For One More Day|For One More Day]]''\n| Pauline Benetto\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2007\u20132011\n| ''[[Big Love]]''\n| Nancy Davis Dutton\n| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Bernie Stabler\n| Episode: \"Swing\"<br>\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Political Animals (miniseries)|Political Animals]]''\n| Margaret Barrish\n| 6 episodes<br>\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Coma (US miniseries)|Coma]]''\n| Mrs. Emerson\n| 2 episodes\n|-South Park \n| 2014\n| ''[[Flowers in the Attic (2014 film)|Flowers in the Attic]]''\n| Olivia Foxworth\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Petals on the Wind#Adaptation|Petals on the Wind]]''\n| Olivia Foxworth\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Louie (U.S. TV series)|Louie]]''\n| Evanka\n| 5 episodes: \"Elevator\" Parts 1, 2, 3, 5, 6\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Mom (TV series)|Mom]]''\n| Shirley Stabler\n| Episode: \"Terrorists and Gingerbread\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[House of Cards (American TV series)|House of Cards]]''\n| Elizabeth Hale\n| 5 episodes\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Nominated work\n!Category\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |1972\n| rowspan=\"4\" |''The Last Picture Show''\n|[[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Nominated\n|<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n|<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/ellen-burstyn|title=Ellen Burstyn|website=www.goldenglobes.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[National Society of Film Critics Award for Best Supporting Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Won\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalsocietyoffilmcritics.com/about-2/|title=Past Awards|date=2009-12-19|website=National Society of Film Critics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[New York Film Critics Circle Award for Best Supporting Actress]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nyfcc.com/awards/|title=Awards - New York Film Critics Circle - NYFCC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1974\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''The Exorcist''\n|[[Academy Award for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Nominated\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Drama]]\n|<ref name=\":9\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |1975\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''Alice Doesn't Live Here Anymore''\n|Academy Award for Best Actress\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Won\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/1976/film/|title=Film in 1976 {{!}} BAFTA Awards|website=awards.bafta.org|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Drama\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":9\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1979\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Same Time, Next Year''\n|Academy Award for Best Actress\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":4\" />\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy]]\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":9\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |1981\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''Resurrection''\n|Academy Award for Best Actress\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Nominated\n|<ref name=\":5\" />\n|-\n|Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Drama\n|<ref name=\":9\" />\n|-\n|[[Saturn Award for Best Actress]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1982\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''The People vs. Jean Harris''\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress \u2013 Miniseries or a Movie|Primetime Emmy Awar